 The next decade, this program was transferred to the Retirement Office, establishing what would become today’s PEHP Health & Benefits.Today, URS and PEHP provide a vast array of employee benefits. URS manages a pension fund worth nearly $26.7 billion, as of Dec. 31, 2015, and serves more than 200,000 members. We administer members’ retirement savings plans worth a total of more than $4.5 billion. PEHP insures more than 125,000 individuals, offering medical, dental, life, LTD, and flexible spending accounts.With about 400+ employees, and under the direction of the URS Board, we continue to serve members in a partnership of trust with a commitment to value, innovation, and excellence.Learn More About URS and PEHPRead moreRead moreWe Are….AccountantsActuariesAdministrative ProfessionalsAnalystsCustomer Service RepresentativesDoctorsEmployer LiaisonsInvestments ProfessionalsIT ProfessionalsLawyersNursesOperations SpecialistsPharmacistsPharmacy TechniciansRetirement Advisors With 400+ employees in Health Insurance and Retirement Savings and Pension we have a position for almost everyone. With plenty of progression opportunities within the organization you have the freedom to explore new opportunities. Read moreWe serve those who serve Utah. Our members come from a diverse range of Utah’s public employers such as: State of Utah, Public and Charter School Systems, Fire Districts, Police Departments, Hogle Zoo, Heber Railroad, Mosquito Abatement Districts, and many more.Read moreUtah Retirement Systems ReviewsUtah Retirement Systems394.1StarStarStarStarStarRating TrendsRating TrendsRecommend to a friendApprove of CEODan Andersen13 Ratings Jun 28, 2017"URS is a great place to work!"StarStarStarStarStarWork/Life BalanceCulture & ValuesCareer OpportunitiesComp & BenefitsSenior ManagementCurrent Employee - Anonymous EmployeeCurrent Employee - Anonymous EmployeeRecommendsPositive OutlookApproves of CEOI have been working at Utah Retirement Systems full-timeProsPositive and frie